        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 6:07PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 607 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles west of Box Elder, or 12 miles northwest of Big Sandy, moving
northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Box Elder.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
